** Cloud Engineer **

QTAC is a not-for-profit organisation that provides and operates an equitable,
centralised tertiary entrance system on behalf of our member and participating
institutions and to provide comprehensive information for prospective
applicants. The institutions that participate in QTAC determine their own
admission requirements and QTAC ensures that these admission rules and
procedures are administered in a transparent, consistent and equitable manner.

Are you an experienced Cloud / DevOps practitioner looking for a change? This
is your opportunity to give back to the community by joining a growing not-
for-profit, community focused organisation that supports young people to
access education prospects.

This exciting and varied position works closely with talented Infrastructure
and project teams supporting BAU and project work. You will provide build and
deployment support to production and project systems, proactive monitoring,
incident management, and issue investigation and resolution, as you enhance
and update business systems and processes.

To be successful in this role you will use your experience in AWS/Azure cloud
environments and use best practice methodologies to optimise our continuous
integration, deployment and delivery pipelines.  
You will drive scalability, automation, innovation and be an enabler for our
software developers, working closely and collaborating with the project team
and the infrastructure team to build and integrate modern tools and best
practices into our environment.

** You will benefit from: **

  * The option for an immediate start 
  * A respected and stable organisation 
  * A positive and rewarding team culture 
  * Up-to-date technology and a modern office environment 
  * Hybrid WFH flexibility 
  * Recognition for success 
  * Being an important member of the Information Technology Services Team, including participating in IT leadership team meetings 
  * Doing work that matters as we pioneer innovative and cutting-edge services to tertiary institutions and year 11 and 12 students 

Our unique QTAC culture - with fun team activities and inclusive social
events, we celebrate achievements and take immense pride and accountability
for the work that we do and the impact we have.

Our culture of growth and development while retaining an inclusive and family
feel, along with work/life balance, will ensure you have the support you need
to make a success of your next career move. Join our fast-paced, and ambitious
organisation and enjoy making a significant impact and being part of our
exciting growth story.

** You will: **

  * Contribute to existing and develop new CI/CD practices for QTAC 
  * Implement / maintain CI/CD tooling and automation processes for both project and production systems 
  * Enhance and build the internal infrastructure platforms 
  * Build and test code with scripting and programming languages 
  * Manage, track and document all change to code and Infrastructure 

** Required Skills and Experience **

** You will have ** : 

  * 12 months experience in a Cloud or DevOps role 
  * Demonstrated ability to lead and support change 
  * Experience with Terraform/Cloud Formation 
  * BASH/Python/NodeJS or similar 
  * Advanced knowledge of AWS services and design principles 
  * AWS Certification highly regarded but not required 
  * Experience working with Agile practices and teams 
  * Linux system administration experience 
  * Networking Background is highly regarded 
  * Experience with logging tools, either open source or commercial 
  * Strong Infrastructure as Code experience (Gitlab/Jenkins/Bitbucket) 
  * Experience with Java, Kubernetes, Docker 
  * AXON Server experience highly regarded 
  * Excellent verbal and written communication 
  * The ability to think critically and troubleshoot proactively 
  * Confidence as a motivated self-starter 

